1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,383
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,383 --> 00:00:02,750
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,250 --> 00:00:06,483
(Episode 23)

4
00:00:18,150 --> 00:00:19,150
What are you doing?

5
00:00:21,083 --> 00:00:23,783
Make some noise before coming in.

6
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:25,483
I did make noise.

7
00:00:25,950 --> 00:00:27,683
You were just too absorbed to hear it.

8
00:00:28,550 --> 00:00:30,683
But why are you drawing scenery
instead of working?

9
00:00:31,950 --> 00:00:33,250
This isn't just a drawing.

10
00:00:33,250 --> 00:00:34,950
This is the first draft of my design.

11
00:00:35,950 --> 00:00:38,250
I may know nothing about architecture,

12
00:00:38,383 --> 00:00:40,583
but how is this a design?
It's a landscape drawing.

13
00:00:41,583 --> 00:00:44,150
Everything about the concept I want
is in this drawing.

14
00:00:44,550 --> 00:00:46,083
You don't see it?

15
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:50,183
Nature and people becoming one.

16
00:00:50,850 --> 00:00:52,383
Is this like the rough sketch
for the retirement community?

17
00:00:53,150 --> 00:00:54,650
Now you finally see it right.

18
00:00:55,150 --> 00:00:57,550
Then where do the buildings go?

19
00:00:57,883 --> 00:01:00,250
Well,
they'll come in when the time is right.

20
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:03,950
What's that?

21
00:01:04,350 --> 00:01:05,850
This? It's gimbap.

22
00:01:06,350 --> 00:01:08,083
My mom made too much,

23
00:01:08,350 --> 00:01:09,983
so I brought some for a late-night snack.

24
00:01:09,983 --> 00:01:12,083
I see, homemade gimbap.

25
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:14,850
Do I happen to get some too?

26
00:01:15,850 --> 00:01:16,883
What? Those slippers!

27
00:01:20,650 --> 00:01:23,150
You said you'd never wear them,
but you're wearing them.

28
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:26,550
Well, my shoes felt uncomfortable today,
so...

29
00:01:26,683 --> 00:01:27,683
I'll throw them away soon.

30
00:01:27,683 --> 00:01:29,550
Who would wear something so childish
in the office?

31
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:31,650
Suit yourself.

32
00:01:32,750 --> 00:01:33,950
Shall we start the meeting?

33
00:01:34,383 --> 00:01:35,383
Yes.

34
00:01:36,750 --> 00:01:37,783
What did Ji Seon say?

35
00:01:38,250 --> 00:01:39,250
Did you talk to her?

36
00:01:39,750 --> 00:01:40,850
I did.

37
00:01:41,750 --> 00:01:43,550
Now it depends on Eun Hyeong.

38
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:50,150
You must've been desperate
to even bring up divorce.

39
00:01:52,250 --> 00:01:53,250
Divorce...

40
00:01:53,850 --> 00:01:55,783
You shouldn't say that lightly.

41
00:01:56,483 --> 00:01:57,850
You're Bit Na's mother.

42
00:01:59,050 --> 00:02:01,450
You know what parents' divorce means
to a child.

43
00:02:02,783 --> 00:02:03,783
I know that too.

44
00:02:07,883 --> 00:02:08,950
I...

45
00:02:10,450 --> 00:02:11,850
held on all this time for one dream,

46
00:02:13,250 --> 00:02:15,450
for Eun Hyeong to become a professor.

47
00:02:16,583 --> 00:02:18,683
When I went back to work
just a month after giving birth,

48
00:02:19,383 --> 00:02:21,083
do you think I was at ease?

49
00:02:23,650 --> 00:02:26,183
Leaving behind a newborn
who woke up crying every three hours,

50
00:02:28,383 --> 00:02:30,150
pumping milk on the plane...

51
00:02:31,250 --> 00:02:32,650
with a breast pump...

52
00:02:33,950 --> 00:02:35,983
How could I not know that?

53
00:02:37,083 --> 00:02:39,650
I know. I know all too well.

54
00:02:40,683 --> 00:02:41,950
I saw so many senior co-workers...

55
00:02:42,850 --> 00:02:44,750
take maternity leave
and then get pushed aside.

56
00:02:45,450 --> 00:02:47,183
I was determined not to end up like that,

57
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,750
and thinking Eun Hyeong would become
a professor soon,

58
00:02:50,850 --> 00:02:52,083
I fought desperately...

59
00:02:53,250 --> 00:02:55,050
to support our family.

60
00:02:56,483 --> 00:02:57,483
Seriously.

61
00:02:58,250 --> 00:02:59,850
If it's not the right path,
he'd rather die than take it.

62
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:01,583
That stubborn personality of his...

63
00:03:02,550 --> 00:03:04,183
really drives you crazy, doesn't it?

64
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:06,350
What I can't stand the most...

65
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:11,350
is that Eun Hyeong seems to think
only his beliefs matter,

66
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:14,183
and our family comes second.

67
00:03:15,083 --> 00:03:16,350
What are you talking about?

68
00:03:16,350 --> 00:03:19,750
To Eun Hyeong, family comes
before anyone else in the world.

69
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:22,283
You know that too.

70
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:28,383
Eun Hyeong will definitely be okay.

71
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:30,183
Ji Seon.

72
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,550
Don't worry too much.

73
00:03:33,483 --> 00:03:34,750
I'm a mother too.

74
00:03:36,850 --> 00:03:38,350
For Bit Na's sake,

75
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:41,350
I'll try harder.

76
00:03:42,150 --> 00:03:45,283
That's right. Mothers are strong.

77
00:03:45,983 --> 00:03:48,450
Let's all get through this together, okay?

78
00:03:49,883 --> 00:03:53,183
Yes, I'll transfer Eun Ae's money today.

79
00:03:53,883 --> 00:03:55,483
I feel so sorry for pressuring her.

80
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:58,983
Is Eun Ae a stranger? She's family.

81
00:04:00,350 --> 00:04:02,750
What did Eun Hyeong say?
Does he have any plan?

82
00:04:03,750 --> 00:04:06,350
As the head of the family,
he says he'll take full responsibility...

83
00:04:06,683 --> 00:04:08,450
and told us not to worry at all.

84
00:04:09,483 --> 00:04:10,783
But the problem remains.

85
00:04:12,383 --> 00:04:14,550
How did Eun Hyeong end up like this?

86
00:04:15,950 --> 00:04:17,383
He never caused trouble growing up...

87
00:04:17,383 --> 00:04:19,283
and was always called a genius.

88
00:04:20,483 --> 00:04:22,383
When it comes to children,
things never go exactly as planned.

89
00:04:26,350 --> 00:04:27,350
Still,

90
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:31,650
I'm so lucky to have you,
who never disappointed me...

91
00:04:32,183 --> 00:04:33,250
once in my life.

92
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:35,350
Thank you, honey.

93
00:04:37,783 --> 00:04:40,583
But where did Eun Ae go?

94
00:04:43,650 --> 00:04:44,650
Yeong Hwa.

95
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:48,250
Yes, what is it?

96
00:04:49,650 --> 00:04:51,050
I will never...

97
00:04:52,150 --> 00:04:57,050
leave you behind.

98
00:04:57,450 --> 00:04:58,450
Okay.

99
00:04:59,683 --> 00:05:03,083
Never leave me behind. Never.

100
00:05:07,450 --> 00:05:08,450
Honey...

101
00:05:10,183 --> 00:05:11,183
Please wake up.

102
00:05:11,650 --> 00:05:12,650
Open your eyes.

103
00:05:13,050 --> 00:05:14,683
Honey, please!

104
00:05:15,750 --> 00:05:16,750
Honey!

105
00:05:17,250 --> 00:05:18,250
Kang Su!

106
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:19,950
Kang Su!

107
00:05:19,950 --> 00:05:21,750
No!

108
00:05:35,850 --> 00:05:39,950
Hello, this is Hani Hotel in Gopyeong...

109
00:05:41,050 --> 00:05:42,150
This is an emergency.

110
00:05:45,450 --> 00:05:48,050
You sure are a bunny.

111
00:05:48,050 --> 00:05:50,450
This gimbap is full of carrots.

112
00:05:51,050 --> 00:05:52,350
Then don't eat it.

113
00:05:52,450 --> 00:05:54,683
This isn't the kind of gimbap...

114
00:05:54,683 --> 00:05:55,850
I get to eat every day.

115
00:05:56,550 --> 00:05:57,683
Who says I won't eat it?

116
00:06:03,750 --> 00:06:05,150
Your mother's cooking is amazing.

117
00:06:05,650 --> 00:06:08,283
Of course,
it can't compare to my grandma's cooking.

118
00:06:09,850 --> 00:06:11,350
You must be really close
to your grandmother.

119
00:06:12,150 --> 00:06:14,450
Last time, you said
your grandmother sang you the lullaby.

120
00:06:14,883 --> 00:06:18,750
Yes. She's the warmest
and most comforting person in my life.

121
00:06:20,783 --> 00:06:22,383
You're not very close with your mom?

122
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:24,850
Usually, people say that about their moms.

123
00:06:27,250 --> 00:06:30,683
Well,
every family has a different atmosphere.

124
00:06:31,550 --> 00:06:35,250
I lost both my paternal
and maternal grandmothers,

125
00:06:35,550 --> 00:06:37,283
so I really envy people
who still have a grandmother.

126
00:06:37,950 --> 00:06:40,150
Though I never even got to see
my maternal grandma's face.

127
00:06:41,450 --> 00:06:42,450
Excuse me.

128
00:06:46,950 --> 00:06:47,950
Hello, Grandma.

129
00:06:50,150 --> 00:06:51,150
What?

130
00:06:51,650 --> 00:06:53,383
They're taking him to the hospital,

131
00:06:53,383 --> 00:06:54,450
so hurry, Gyeol.

132
00:06:54,850 --> 00:06:56,650
Yes, I'll leave right away.

133
00:06:58,650 --> 00:06:59,683
What's wrong, Team Manager?

134
00:07:00,183 --> 00:07:02,650
My grandpa is being taken to the hospital.

135
00:07:02,650 --> 00:07:05,250
Which hospital? I'll give you a ride.

136
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:08,850
What do you mean?
What happened to your grandpa?

137
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:12,850
Okay, I'm leaving right now.

138
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:15,383
What is it? Who was that?

139
00:07:15,583 --> 00:07:16,650
It was Gyeol.

140
00:07:17,083 --> 00:07:18,750
Father collapsed with a high fever.

141
00:07:18,750 --> 00:07:20,250
They're taking him to the hospital now.

142
00:07:20,750 --> 00:07:21,750
Get ready, hurry!

143
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:23,850
What do we do?

144
00:07:24,183 --> 00:07:25,883
I'm bare-faced right now!

145
00:07:26,283 --> 00:07:28,650
Does that matter right now? Hurry!

146
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:32,550
I asked you to have coffee with me,
and you want to have instant coffee here?

147
00:07:33,150 --> 00:07:34,150
What?

148
00:07:34,850 --> 00:07:35,850
When did he come?

149
00:07:36,383 --> 00:07:38,250
He went on a trip with Grandpa today.

150
00:07:42,083 --> 00:07:43,983
What? Ms. Cho is here too?

151
00:07:55,650 --> 00:07:56,650
Wait, what?

152
00:07:57,650 --> 00:08:00,583
Did they have a gimbap date
in the office or something?

153
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:03,650
Wait.

154
00:08:05,950 --> 00:08:06,950
Hi, Dad.

155
00:08:08,350 --> 00:08:09,350
What?

156
00:08:10,350 --> 00:08:11,783
(Haedeul Hospital)

157
00:08:14,483 --> 00:08:15,483
Grandma!

158
00:08:17,950 --> 00:08:19,350
Grandma, what happened?

159
00:08:20,450 --> 00:08:23,250
Maybe getting some fresh air
was too much for him.

160
00:08:25,883 --> 00:08:28,083
He shouldn't have taken me to see flowers.

161
00:08:29,183 --> 00:08:30,450
What do we do?

162
00:08:30,983 --> 00:08:32,650
If he doesn't wake up...

163
00:08:33,683 --> 00:08:34,683
Grandma.

164
00:08:37,350 --> 00:08:38,350
Who...

165
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,750
Hello.

166
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:44,250
I'm Cho Eun Ae,
an intern on Team Manager Ko's team.

167
00:08:45,283 --> 00:08:47,883
We were in a meeting together,
and she gave me a ride here.

168
00:08:47,883 --> 00:08:48,883
I see.

169
00:08:53,050 --> 00:08:54,050
Wait, miss...

170
00:08:54,950 --> 00:08:56,650
You're the one who installed Joy for me...

171
00:08:56,750 --> 00:08:57,750
Joy...

172
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:59,250
Ma'am!

173
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:01,883
You're Team Manager's Grandma?

174
00:09:06,483 --> 00:09:07,850
- Mother!
- Mother!

175
00:09:08,483 --> 00:09:10,050
What on earth happened?

176
00:09:12,283 --> 00:09:14,550
Where on earth did you take them,
you punk?

177
00:09:15,083 --> 00:09:17,083
And you should've taken responsibility
to the end!

178
00:09:17,650 --> 00:09:18,950
It's not Gyeol's fault.

179
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:21,750
You know your father's condition,
so why are you saying that?

180
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:22,850
Of course it is.

181
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,750
He was perfectly fine when you left.

182
00:09:25,950 --> 00:09:27,850
Last time too, when he was with Gyeol...

183
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:32,850
Why do they always blame poor Gyeol
for everything?

184
00:09:32,850 --> 00:09:33,850
Seriously.

185
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:35,183
Doctor.

186
00:09:39,083 --> 00:09:40,350
It's acute pneumonia.

187
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:42,550
Thankfully, he's past the critical stage.

188
00:09:43,883 --> 00:09:45,250
Thank you, Doctor.

189
00:09:48,850 --> 00:09:50,150
We'll observe him for a few more hours,

190
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:52,483
and if he stabilizes,
we'll move him to a room.

191
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,750
He needs as much rest as possible,

192
00:09:55,250 --> 00:09:58,350
so only one or two people should stay.
Everyone else, please go home.

193
00:10:00,950 --> 00:10:03,950
Everyone, go home. I'll stay here.

194
00:10:03,950 --> 00:10:05,250
I'll stay, Grandma.

195
00:10:05,750 --> 00:10:08,183
You pushed yourself too hard today,
so you need rest too.

196
00:10:08,183 --> 00:10:09,250
What are you talking about?

197
00:10:09,583 --> 00:10:11,750
Min Ho and I, his son and eldest grandson,
should be the ones to stay.

198
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:15,250
You go home.

199
00:10:16,183 --> 00:10:19,250
And who is this young lady
who's been standing there this whole time?

200
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:21,383
Hello.

201
00:10:21,750 --> 00:10:23,650
I'm on Team Manager Ko Gyeol's team.

202
00:10:23,783 --> 00:10:26,783
Wait, you're Seong Jun's daughter, right?

203
00:10:27,383 --> 00:10:28,583
Yes.

204
00:10:29,783 --> 00:10:31,150
The cleaner friend's daughter?

205
00:10:33,083 --> 00:10:35,150
I feel like I've seen you somewhere.

206
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:36,183
Where did I see you?

207
00:10:36,183 --> 00:10:37,183
Mom.

208
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:38,550
Min Ho.

209
00:10:40,150 --> 00:10:41,250
Seung Ri, you came too?

210
00:10:41,783 --> 00:10:44,850
Why are all these unrelated people here?

211
00:10:45,383 --> 00:10:47,450
Dad, please take Mom back home.

212
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:50,150
We'll stay here
and take turns with Grandma.

213
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:51,750
Yeah, let's go, honey.

214
00:10:51,850 --> 00:10:54,250
I can't stay overnight at a hospital.

215
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:57,383
Mother, I'll come back
first thing tomorrow morning.

216
00:10:58,050 --> 00:10:59,583
Please call me right away
if anything happens.

217
00:10:59,783 --> 00:11:01,150
All right, do that.

218
00:11:01,350 --> 00:11:02,350
Then, Mother,

219
00:11:02,450 --> 00:11:03,850
please take care of things here.

220
00:11:05,883 --> 00:11:06,950
Honey, I feel dizzy.

221
00:11:06,950 --> 00:11:07,983
Come here, let's go.

222
00:11:09,750 --> 00:11:11,250
He'll be fine.

223
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:13,250
Please stay strong, okay?

224
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:17,983
Come with me to the room.

225
00:11:17,983 --> 00:11:19,550
They said Grandpa will be moved up soon.

226
00:11:19,750 --> 00:11:21,350
- Yes, let's do that.
- Yes.

227
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:23,383
Thank you, miss.

228
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:26,450
Not at all. I hope he gets better soon.

229
00:11:26,883 --> 00:11:28,183
You must've been really shocked.

230
00:11:28,183 --> 00:11:29,850
He'll get better soon.

231
00:11:30,050 --> 00:11:32,750
Yes, Seung Ri. Thank you for coming.

232
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:33,750
Wait a moment.

233
00:11:34,050 --> 00:11:35,450
I'll take Grandma back first.

234
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:37,683
No, I should get going now.

235
00:11:38,383 --> 00:11:39,383
All right, then.

236
00:11:39,383 --> 00:11:41,250
- Thank you for today.
- Yes.

237
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:42,250
Let's go, Grandma.

238
00:11:46,683 --> 00:11:47,683
I'll get going.

239
00:11:47,950 --> 00:11:48,950
Wait here just a little.

240
00:11:49,383 --> 00:11:51,950
I'll go up to the room for a moment,
then take you both home.

241
00:11:51,950 --> 00:11:54,883
No, it's okay. I have my scooter.

242
00:11:54,883 --> 00:11:55,883
I see.

243
00:11:56,950 --> 00:11:58,483
Manager Seo, wait here for a bit.

244
00:12:04,083 --> 00:12:05,083
Goodbye...

245
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:06,850
Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

246
00:12:07,650 --> 00:12:09,050
Can I talk to you for a moment?

247
00:12:13,050 --> 00:12:15,350
What do you mean?

248
00:12:16,050 --> 00:12:17,350
I don't quite understand...

249
00:12:17,550 --> 00:12:19,150
why you are here.

250
00:12:20,050 --> 00:12:21,750
Why would you come
to a place where only family is gathered?

251
00:12:22,950 --> 00:12:24,250
I just...

252
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:27,050
gave Team Manager a ride
because he looked like...

253
00:12:27,050 --> 00:12:28,750
he was in a real hurry.

254
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,283
Then you should've left right away.

255
00:12:31,650 --> 00:12:33,383
I saw the pantry was a mess too.

256
00:12:33,983 --> 00:12:36,183
I was actually about to go back
and clean it.

257
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:41,050
But you're not family either, Manager,
so why were you...

258
00:12:45,350 --> 00:12:47,750
I'm sorry. That was my mistake.

259
00:12:51,350 --> 00:12:54,150
So you were here.
I thought you had already left.

260
00:12:54,583 --> 00:12:56,250
I'll get going now.

261
00:12:56,850 --> 00:12:57,850
Be careful on your way home.

262
00:13:02,850 --> 00:13:04,350
I'm leaving. See you at work.

263
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:05,350
Why?

264
00:13:05,850 --> 00:13:07,250
I said I'd take you home.

265
00:13:07,383 --> 00:13:09,350
No, I'll go by myself.

266
00:13:14,483 --> 00:13:16,850
So while you were eating gimbap...

267
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:18,550
together in the office,

268
00:13:19,083 --> 00:13:20,583
you went to the hospital...

269
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:23,250
where Team Manager's grandfather,
the Chairman of Kangsu Group, was?

270
00:13:23,650 --> 00:13:25,950
Yeah, he was in a hurry,
so I gave him a ride.

271
00:13:26,983 --> 00:13:29,883
Then Team Manager must've held your waist
from behind!

272
00:13:31,650 --> 00:13:34,150
This feels like a green light.

273
00:13:34,450 --> 00:13:35,450
Don't be ridiculous.

274
00:13:36,050 --> 00:13:39,750
More importantly, Manager Seo
has been acting a little strange lately.

275
00:13:40,450 --> 00:13:42,450
How? Is she giving you a hard time?

276
00:13:42,450 --> 00:13:45,150
No, I'd say she's gotten more sensitive.

277
00:13:45,850 --> 00:13:47,550
Even earlier at the hospital,

278
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:50,483
she asked why I was there
where only family should be.

279
00:13:50,850 --> 00:13:53,883
That's all because of the love triangle.

280
00:13:54,483 --> 00:13:56,083
Red likes Orange,

281
00:13:56,083 --> 00:13:57,650
Orange likes Gray,

282
00:13:57,650 --> 00:13:59,283
- and Gray...
- Love triangle?

283
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:02,050
Then like you said...

284
00:14:02,450 --> 00:14:04,450
Manager's arrow points to Team Manager?

285
00:14:04,750 --> 00:14:06,483
You're quick to notice, aren't you?

286
00:14:07,050 --> 00:14:09,250
No way, it's a complete misunderstanding.

287
00:14:09,750 --> 00:14:10,750
What do I do?

288
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:12,050
I don't think it's a misunderstanding.

289
00:14:12,450 --> 00:14:14,050
Think carefully.

290
00:14:14,050 --> 00:14:15,050
Team Manager's arrow...

291
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:18,183
It's stuck in you.

292
00:14:18,183 --> 00:14:19,250
No way.

293
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:22,050
My team manager only thinks about...

294
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:23,250
how to make my life miserable.

295
00:14:23,250 --> 00:14:25,583
Cho Eun Ae, back when we were little,

296
00:14:25,583 --> 00:14:28,750
remember that kid who'd always
snap the jump rope and run away?

297
00:14:28,950 --> 00:14:30,383
That snot-nosed Byeong Cheol?

298
00:14:30,383 --> 00:14:32,983
Yeah, that was all because he liked me...

299
00:14:32,983 --> 00:14:34,483
and wanted my attention.

300
00:14:34,883 --> 00:14:36,250
He liked you?

301
00:14:36,950 --> 00:14:39,250
See? This is why you're so dense.

302
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:42,450
Anyway, what about your arrow?

303
00:14:42,750 --> 00:14:43,750
My arrow?

304
00:14:44,683 --> 00:14:45,750
I don't have one.

305
00:14:46,383 --> 00:14:47,383
Actually, I do.

306
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:49,650
My arrow points to Joy.

307
00:14:50,150 --> 00:14:51,283
Stop joking.

308
00:14:51,783 --> 00:14:55,083
I think your arrow points
to Team Manager too.

309
00:14:57,850 --> 00:15:01,183
Are you two going to stay up all night
talking about love triangles?

310
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,850
Did we wake you up?

311
00:15:03,850 --> 00:15:06,183
Sorry, Grandma. Good night.

312
00:15:06,750 --> 00:15:08,550
- I'm leaving.
- Bye.

313
00:15:09,450 --> 00:15:11,383
Think carefully about your arrow too.

314
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:13,550
Okay? Whoosh.

315
00:15:19,250 --> 00:15:20,550
- Mother!
- Mother!

316
00:15:21,183 --> 00:15:22,850
What on earth happened?

317
00:15:25,050 --> 00:15:27,083
Where on earth did you take them?

318
00:15:27,350 --> 00:15:29,750
And you should've taken responsibility
to the end!

319
00:15:29,950 --> 00:15:31,083
It's not Gyeol's fault.

320
00:15:32,050 --> 00:15:33,950
You know your father's condition,
so why are you saying that?

321
00:15:33,950 --> 00:15:35,050
Of course it is.

322
00:15:35,450 --> 00:15:37,983
He was perfectly fine when you left.

323
00:15:38,150 --> 00:15:39,983
Last time too, when he was with Gyeol...

324
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:43,750
What could it be?

325
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:46,050
Is Team Manager also an ugly duckling
like me?

326
00:15:46,750 --> 00:15:49,450
You grew up with a silver spoon...

327
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:52,350
in a perfect family full of love.

328
00:15:53,350 --> 00:15:54,883
What kind of wound
could you possibly have?

329
00:15:56,350 --> 00:16:00,083
Have you ever heard that
what you see isn't everything?

330
00:16:02,450 --> 00:16:04,083
Could Team Manager really have...

331
00:16:04,350 --> 00:16:06,550
wounds other people can't see?

332
00:16:08,850 --> 00:16:10,383
I don't care whether he does or not!

333
00:16:14,216 --> 00:16:15,450
Did you get home okay?

334
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:17,650
Thank you for today. I owe you a lot.

335
00:16:18,250 --> 00:16:19,483
I'll pay you back someday.

336
00:16:20,583 --> 00:16:21,883
It was nothing.

337
00:16:22,883 --> 00:16:25,550
You looked really troubled.
Are you okay...

338
00:16:27,450 --> 00:16:28,450
Cho Eun Ae.

339
00:16:28,450 --> 00:16:30,550
Why do you keep worrying
about Team Manager?

340
00:16:31,650 --> 00:16:33,750
The person I should really worry about
is Manager Seo.

341
00:16:35,783 --> 00:16:37,950
How do I clear up this misunderstanding?

342
00:16:41,350 --> 00:16:42,450
The Chairman is at the hospital?

343
00:16:43,050 --> 00:16:45,083
- Honey, please get my jacket.
- Okay.

344
00:16:45,083 --> 00:16:46,783
- Then I'll head in.
- Okay.

345
00:16:49,250 --> 00:16:50,250
It's me, sir.

346
00:16:50,983 --> 00:16:52,350
What happened to the Chairman?

347
00:16:53,050 --> 00:16:54,050
I'll head to the hospital right now...

348
00:16:54,050 --> 00:16:56,050
Why would you go there?
No outsiders are allowed.

349
00:16:56,383 --> 00:16:57,450
No outsiders are allowed?

350
00:16:57,450 --> 00:16:58,750
Then what are you? An insider?

351
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,883
Are you family or something?
I'm hanging up.

352
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:07,150
What did he say?
They said no outsiders allowed?

353
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:09,850
Unbelievable, seriously.

354
00:17:10,783 --> 00:17:11,850
To Dae Chi,

355
00:17:12,183 --> 00:17:14,650
once the Chairman is gone,
you'll be nothing.

356
00:17:15,183 --> 00:17:17,683
Before that, you need to settle things
with the Chairman somehow.

357
00:17:18,350 --> 00:17:19,750
Even if it's just one small subsidiary...

358
00:17:22,950 --> 00:17:24,450
Listen to me for once!

359
00:17:29,450 --> 00:17:30,883
What's with you now?

360
00:17:34,250 --> 00:17:36,850
You're all hopeless.

361
00:17:41,183 --> 00:17:42,750
I seriously can't believe it.

362
00:17:43,383 --> 00:17:44,483
My soulmate,

363
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:48,550
Oh My Oz, is that crazy girl?

364
00:17:56,883 --> 00:17:58,683
(Story World Community)

365
00:18:02,383 --> 00:18:04,083
Seriously.

366
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:09,583
You perverted psycho.

367
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:13,083
You're forever out of my life.

368
00:18:13,583 --> 00:18:15,750
(Delete account, Confirm deletion)

369
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:16,450
(Account deleted)

370
00:18:20,450 --> 00:18:21,450
It's done.

371
00:18:23,283 --> 00:18:24,850
Yeah, you crazy girl.

372
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:28,050
You are forever out of my life now.

373
00:18:28,050 --> 00:18:28,550
(Delete account)

374
00:18:44,150 --> 00:18:45,583
(The moment she said that,
Do Yeon almost lost her breath...)

375
00:18:55,350 --> 00:18:56,350
Hello, Producer.

376
00:18:58,383 --> 00:18:59,983
What did you say?

377
00:19:01,883 --> 00:19:04,883
That web novel writer...

378
00:19:05,850 --> 00:19:08,350
is the author of "The ER Witch?"

379
00:19:08,983 --> 00:19:10,050
This is your last chance.

380
00:19:10,450 --> 00:19:11,750
Go, get on your knees,

381
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:13,583
and beg desperately if you have to.

382
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:20,650
Seriously...

383
00:19:21,383 --> 00:19:22,850
Darn it!

384
00:19:28,150 --> 00:19:29,283
Why?

385
00:19:30,550 --> 00:19:33,850
Why do you keep giving me these trials?

386
00:19:36,350 --> 00:19:37,350
Seriously.

387
00:19:40,050 --> 00:19:41,583
(Haedeul Hospital)

388
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:48,683
Please open your eyes.

389
00:19:50,650 --> 00:19:52,950
Open your eyes and call my name again.

390
00:19:53,650 --> 00:19:55,383
Kang Su, please.

391
00:20:06,950 --> 00:20:08,150
Where are you, Yeon Sun?

392
00:20:09,150 --> 00:20:10,183
Yeon Sun!

393
00:20:12,983 --> 00:20:14,083
Why is she there? It's dangerous.

394
00:20:22,350 --> 00:20:24,250
- Yeon Sun!
- Mom!

395
00:20:24,250 --> 00:20:25,250
Yeon Sun.

396
00:20:26,950 --> 00:20:27,983
Yeon Sun.

397
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:32,250
The hospital...

398
00:20:32,650 --> 00:20:33,850
Fire!

399
00:20:33,850 --> 00:20:34,850
Move!

400
00:20:34,883 --> 00:20:35,883
- Move!
- This first...

401
00:20:38,450 --> 00:20:39,450
Yeon Sun!

402
00:20:40,983 --> 00:20:43,850
Yeon Sun, wake up. It's Mom.

403
00:20:44,383 --> 00:20:46,483
Yeon Sun, wake up! It's Mom.

404
00:20:47,450 --> 00:20:48,950
Yeon Sun!

405
00:20:52,883 --> 00:20:54,450
To the hospital. Hurry!

406
00:20:55,383 --> 00:20:56,383
Yeon Sun!

407
00:20:57,350 --> 00:20:58,350
Yeon Sun!

408
00:21:02,183 --> 00:21:05,450
If it weren't for you back then,

409
00:21:06,783 --> 00:21:09,783
if you hadn't been there, my Yeon Sun...

410
00:21:10,750 --> 00:21:11,783
Yeon Sun...

411
00:21:23,450 --> 00:21:25,550
Why are you crying, Yeong Hwa?

412
00:21:26,450 --> 00:21:27,850
Honey!

413
00:21:28,650 --> 00:21:29,783
Are you awake?

414
00:21:30,583 --> 00:21:31,883
Don't cry.

415
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:35,250
It hurts my heart.

416
00:21:35,483 --> 00:21:38,450
Okay, I won't cry.

417
00:21:39,383 --> 00:21:42,283
Why would I cry when you've woken up?

418
00:21:43,183 --> 00:21:45,050
I'll go get Dr. Kim.

419
00:21:45,150 --> 00:21:46,150
No.

420
00:21:47,083 --> 00:21:48,150
I want to talk...

421
00:21:49,783 --> 00:21:51,883
with you a little more, Yeong Hwa.

422
00:21:52,483 --> 00:21:55,050
You can take your time speaking.

423
00:21:57,983 --> 00:21:58,983
I'm sorry.

424
00:22:00,650 --> 00:22:01,683
Because of me,

425
00:22:03,050 --> 00:22:05,583
the flower trip we'd been
looking forward to for so long...

426
00:22:06,983 --> 00:22:08,250
was completely ruined.

427
00:22:08,983 --> 00:22:09,983
No.

428
00:22:11,250 --> 00:22:14,150
Just having you wake up like this
is more than enough for me.

429
00:22:14,850 --> 00:22:16,650
Don't feel sorry at all.

430
00:22:22,250 --> 00:22:23,250
Grandpa.

431
00:22:25,850 --> 00:22:26,850
You're awake?

432
00:22:28,383 --> 00:22:31,250
I'm sorry.
I should've paid more attention.

433
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:33,583
What are you talking about?

434
00:22:35,050 --> 00:22:36,750
It was perfect.

435
00:22:38,583 --> 00:22:42,150
I'm the one who's sorry
for making you worry.

436
00:22:44,550 --> 00:22:46,250
Don't say that, Grandpa.

437
00:22:48,183 --> 00:22:49,650
I have a favor to ask.

438
00:22:50,983 --> 00:22:53,150
Take your grandma home.

439
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:57,650
She probably hasn't slept a wink
all night.

440
00:22:58,450 --> 00:22:59,950
What are you saying?

441
00:23:00,583 --> 00:23:03,050
I should go home with you
after you're discharged.

442
00:23:04,050 --> 00:23:06,083
I'm awake now, aren't I?

443
00:23:07,250 --> 00:23:11,583
I'll obviously have to stay hospitalized
for a few more days.

444
00:23:13,083 --> 00:23:14,850
Please, just listen to me.

445
00:23:16,650 --> 00:23:19,050
He's right, Grandma.

446
00:23:19,450 --> 00:23:20,550
Come home with me.

447
00:23:21,350 --> 00:23:22,350
Okay.

448
00:23:23,083 --> 00:23:26,150
I'll rest a little
and come back this afternoon.

449
00:23:27,183 --> 00:23:29,350
Call Mr. Seo.

450
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:31,750
Tell him to come see me.

451
00:23:31,850 --> 00:23:33,683
He's already waiting outside.

452
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:35,150
I'll tell him to come in right away.

453
00:23:35,850 --> 00:23:36,850
Let's go, Grandma.

454
00:23:56,650 --> 00:23:57,683
I'm sorry, Chairman.

455
00:23:58,083 --> 00:23:59,650
It's because I failed to stay
by your side.

456
00:23:59,650 --> 00:24:01,450
Why would that be your fault?

457
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:04,250
For once,

458
00:24:05,483 --> 00:24:08,150
I wanted you to get some proper rest too,

459
00:24:09,550 --> 00:24:11,650
but my body wouldn't cooperate.

460
00:24:15,783 --> 00:24:16,950
I don't think...

461
00:24:18,350 --> 00:24:20,050
I have as much time as I thought.

462
00:24:22,850 --> 00:24:24,350
How is it going?

463
00:24:26,450 --> 00:24:29,383
Among the overseas adoptees,
we've narrowed it down to...

464
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:31,450
about ten children who match
the timing, age, and gender.

465
00:24:32,350 --> 00:24:34,183
Hurry, somehow.

466
00:24:36,050 --> 00:24:37,650
I can't bear the thought...

467
00:24:39,350 --> 00:24:42,583
of leaving her behind all alone
and closing my eyes.

468
00:24:44,150 --> 00:24:46,383
Yes, I'll hurry, Chairman.

469
00:24:47,050 --> 00:24:48,350
Don't lose heart.

470
00:24:50,750 --> 00:24:51,750
Father!

471
00:24:53,450 --> 00:24:54,750
Father, are you feeling a little better?

472
00:24:55,450 --> 00:24:57,550
I thought something terrible
might've happened to you.

473
00:24:58,483 --> 00:25:00,350
Why are you making such a fuss again?

474
00:25:01,950 --> 00:25:04,483
I could go any day now.

475
00:25:05,950 --> 00:25:10,050
Why make such a big deal
over me collapsing from a little fever?

476
00:25:10,583 --> 00:25:12,450
Father, please don't say that.

477
00:25:12,450 --> 00:25:14,983
You saying that to me, your only son,

478
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:16,750
is truly too cruel.

479
00:25:27,583 --> 00:25:29,883
(Kangsu Construction)

480
00:25:37,950 --> 00:25:39,550
Should our team go out for lunch?

481
00:25:40,783 --> 00:25:43,083
I'm sorry. I already have lunch plans.

482
00:25:43,783 --> 00:25:45,583
Really? Well, it can't be helped.

483
00:25:46,183 --> 00:25:47,383
You're okay with it, right, Ms. Cho?

484
00:25:47,383 --> 00:25:49,283
As thanks for making me gimbap last time,
I'll...

485
00:25:49,950 --> 00:25:50,950
Team Manager!

486
00:25:52,983 --> 00:25:54,883
I didn't make that gimbap.

487
00:25:57,450 --> 00:25:59,150
My mom just made too much,

488
00:25:59,150 --> 00:26:01,150
so I brought the leftovers.

489
00:26:03,383 --> 00:26:05,250
Yes, but still.

490
00:26:08,450 --> 00:26:09,850
I need to talk to you, Team Manager.

491
00:26:22,450 --> 00:26:23,650
What is going on?

492
00:26:24,350 --> 00:26:25,350
You still don't get it?

493
00:26:25,950 --> 00:26:27,650
They are totally in the talking stage.

494
00:26:27,650 --> 00:26:29,383
Not talking stage, fighting stage.

495
00:26:29,950 --> 00:26:31,550
Can't you see them
constantly going at each other?

496
00:26:32,283 --> 00:26:34,650
Why are you getting so worked up, Mr. Han?

497
00:26:35,450 --> 00:26:36,950
I'm going to stop by the CPO's office,

498
00:26:36,950 --> 00:26:38,150
so go have lunch.

499
00:26:38,450 --> 00:26:40,050
What are you saying?

500
00:26:40,450 --> 00:26:42,850
You still don't understand?

501
00:26:44,050 --> 00:26:45,550
How should I explain this?

502
00:26:46,350 --> 00:26:47,450
Look.

503
00:26:48,750 --> 00:26:50,383
(CPO, Manager Seo, Team Manager)

504
00:26:51,850 --> 00:26:55,250
Right now, the CPO likes Manager Seo,

505
00:26:55,450 --> 00:26:57,183
and Manager Seo likes you, Team Manager.

506
00:26:57,450 --> 00:26:58,983
This is the current situation.

507
00:26:59,550 --> 00:27:01,650
And the problem is that your arrow...

508
00:27:02,183 --> 00:27:04,650
seems like it might be pointing at me...

509
00:27:04,950 --> 00:27:07,583
Like maybe, maybe not.

510
00:27:08,250 --> 00:27:11,950
Of course, I know it's not actually me,

511
00:27:12,350 --> 00:27:13,983
but at least
from Manager Seo's perspective...

512
00:27:14,683 --> 00:27:15,683
So?

513
00:27:16,250 --> 00:27:18,850
Why are you so clueless?

514
00:27:19,550 --> 00:27:20,650
Because of your vague,

515
00:27:20,650 --> 00:27:22,650
wishy-washy, maybe-maybe-not attitude,

516
00:27:23,050 --> 00:27:25,450
I'm the only one suffering here.

517
00:27:26,950 --> 00:27:27,950
Wait a second.

518
00:27:29,083 --> 00:27:31,383
These three have lines... No.

519
00:27:31,883 --> 00:27:34,050
The love arrows you're talking about...

520
00:27:34,650 --> 00:27:36,583
You're the only one without one.

521
00:27:36,950 --> 00:27:39,050
Me? My arrow?

522
00:27:39,350 --> 00:27:42,383
Where is your arrow pointing, Ms. Cho?

523
00:27:43,083 --> 00:27:44,450
Well...

524
00:27:46,250 --> 00:27:47,250
Tell me.

525
00:27:48,483 --> 00:27:51,983
Where is your arrow pointing right now?

526
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:07,983
(Our Happy Days)

527
00:28:08,050 --> 00:28:10,850
The soybean paste stew here
is really good, Gyeol.

528
00:28:11,650 --> 00:28:13,050
Seriously, you have no sense at all.

529
00:28:13,050 --> 00:28:14,350
So where exactly...

530
00:28:14,350 --> 00:28:16,150
is your arrow pointing right now? Hurry.

531
00:28:16,150 --> 00:28:18,250
"The ER Witch"
is my all-time favorite work.

532
00:28:18,483 --> 00:28:20,083
What if I were the one to draw it?

533
00:28:20,350 --> 00:28:22,583
I can't do it! Do it!

534
00:28:22,583 --> 00:28:25,450
The password to my safe
is that child's birthday.

535
00:28:25,450 --> 00:28:26,450
That child's birthday?

536
00:28:27,150 --> 00:28:28,783
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
